  <p>Scroll a Filipino football fan's feed in the run-up to kickoff and the offers arrive faster than the match previews. Leaderboard competitions. Points you earn by betting. Daily rewards. Prize draws dangling smartphones, tablets, gaming consoles, smartwatches, and cash awards climbing as high as 10,000 dollars. These are not the promotions of PAGCOR-licensed operators — they cannot be, because licensed operators are now legally barred from being this generous. The most aggressive World Cup betting offers reaching Filipinos are coming, almost by design, from the operators with no Philippine license to lose.</p>

